  "body": "#### Description\r\n\r\n\"Modal should go to the full height of the window (**but with a 64px margin top and bottom**) if the window isn't tall enough to display the modal content without scrolling\" @John-44 \r\n\r\n#### Solution proposal\r\n- ~~every popup should be opened through `Global.openPopup`~~\r\n- ~~`Global.openPopup` should contain logic that calculates the size and position of the modal to fulfill the above constraints (this may not be that straightforward having in mind Popup should resize itself to its optimal size when Window is enlarged again)~~\r\n-  ~~**this new logic should not affect how popups deduce their optimal size from contentItem**, in other words: popups should not make any assumptions about how `Global.openPopup` works~~",
